headline: Morgan Stanley Reports Fourth Quarter and Full Year 2025 Earnings Results
summary: NEW YORK, January 15, 2026--Morgan Stanley (NYSE: MS) today announced its fourth quarter and full year 2025 financial results. The results are now available on the Firm’s Investor Relations website at www.morganstanley.com/about-us-ir/earnings-releases. The results will be filed on a Form 8-K with the Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC) on January 15, 2026, which will be available on the SEC’s website at www.sec.gov.

headline: Morgan Stanley Rakes in New Assets as It Rides Bull Market for Stocks

headline: Morgan Stanley and Goldman Sachs Stocks Rise
summary: Shares of Morgan Stanley and Goldman Sachs were up 4.1% and 2.25%, respectively, early Thursday morning after the companies reported better-than-expected fourth-quarter earnings.  Morgan Stanley’s wealth management unit shined during the quarter and hauled in an impressive $122 billion in net new assets—a 116% increase from the same period a year ago.  Goldman Sachs fourth-quarter net earnings came in at $4.62 billion.

headline: Morgan Stanley CEO Downplays Acquisition Possibilities; The Bar is ‘High’
summary: Morgan Stanley CEO Ted Pick told analysts Thursday morning that the bar for future acquisitions is high and that excess capital might be better returned to shareholders in the form of dividends.  “We are endeavoring to keep the bar for acquisitions high,” Pick said during the company’s earnings call.  Pick, who became CEO a year ago, said Morgan Stanley knows firsthand how much effort is required to integrate newly acquired companies.

headline: Morgan Stanley (NYSE:MS) Surprises With Q4 CY2025 Sales
